Coloration: (Most of the specimens have been preserved for more than 50 years.) Body light brown with many small, black spots, abdomen and branchial cavity bluish and eyes blue with lighter lens. In a few specimens darker brown epidermis remains. The unripe 57 mm specimen (
Fig. 8
) has a much more dense pigmentation all over head and body, maybe a subadult character.
